Right, Pops?

1026
00:55:52,877 --> 00:55:54,245
Yeah, yeah. I concur.

1027
00:55:54,345 --> 00:55:55,712
Come on, guys.

1028
00:55:57,982 --> 00:55:59,217
What are they doing?

1029
00:55:59,751 --> 00:56:01,352
Making your car faster.

1030
00:56:09,127 --> 00:56:10,228
There. Right there.

1031
00:56:10,328 --> 00:56:11,595
Airflow's getting stuck.

1032
00:56:14,598 --> 00:56:17,435
I see it.
Yarn blows straight up.

1033
00:56:17,535 --> 00:56:19,080
- Yep.
- The front's lifting.

1034
00:56:19,104 --> 00:56:20,738
Damn, he's right.

1035
00:56:31,216 --> 00:56:34,552
This car wants to go faster.
I feel it.

1036
00:56:34,651 --> 00:56:36,554
Any lighter,
we're getting fragile.

1037
00:56:37,021 --> 00:56:38,923
Took 70 pounds out of her
in the last week.

1038
00:56:39,023 --> 00:56:41,826
She's outputting max horsepower
from this displacement.

1039
00:56:41,926 --> 00:56:44,095
So put in a bigger engine.

1040
00:56:44,195 --> 00:56:45,997
Where we gonna put it?
On the roof?

1041
00:56:48,933 --> 00:56:50,677
Managed to make it
52 pounds lighter

1042
00:56:50,701 --> 00:56:52,669
than the NASCAR unit.

1043
00:56:57,108 --> 00:56:59,577
All-new aluminum
cylinder heads...

1044
00:57:00,245 --> 00:57:03,448
vibration dampeners,
water pump, smaller valves.

1045
00:57:03,781 --> 00:57:05,283
We call it the Beast.

1046
00:57:05,917 --> 00:57:07,218
Yeah, I can see why,

1047
00:57:07,318 --> 00:57:08,419
but how's it gonna fit

1048
00:57:08,520 --> 00:57:10,488
without a redesign
of the engine bed?

1049
00:57:10,588 --> 00:57:11,765
Well, it certainly
wasn't easy.

1050
00:57:11,789 --> 00:57:13,033
Good morning, gentlemen.
Mr. Shelby.

1051
00:57:13,057 --> 00:57:17,195
So, you already put that
in a GT40?

1052
00:57:17,495 --> 00:57:19,696
I'm afraid we have.

1053
00:57:25,303 --> 00:57:26,838
I'll be damned.

1054
00:57:27,405 --> 00:57:28,773
Well, it's heavy, of course.

1055
00:57:28,873 --> 00:57:30,217
Problems with the handling,
especially the stopping.

1056
00:57:30,241 --> 00:57:32,377
- I can show you the data.
- What problems?

1057
00:57:32,477 --> 00:57:33,611
Understeers a little, but...

1058
00:57:33,710 --> 00:57:35,313
Can I borrow that?

1059
00:57:35,413 --> 00:57:36,614
Just a second. Thank you.

1060
00:57:36,713 --> 00:57:37,713
Ken!

1061
00:57:38,416 --> 00:57:41,619
Ken, perhaps you want to check
with HQ before you test...

1062
00:57:41,718 --> 00:57:43,087
What did he say?

1063
00:57:43,188 --> 00:57:44,431
We should ask...

1064
00:57:44,455 --> 00:57:45,689
Right.

1065
00:57:47,859 --> 00:57:50,995
Oh, yes!

1066
00:57:58,136 --> 00:58:00,638
Mr. Shelby,
welcome to Dearborn.

1067
00:58:00,738 --> 00:58:02,106
What are you doing
at a test track?

1068
00:58:02,207 --> 00:58:04,442
You're gonna get Castrol oil
all over that nice suit.

1069
00:58:04,542 --> 00:58:05,862
Ah, I wanted to hear
your thoughts

1070
00:58:05,910 --> 00:58:07,030
on a few planning decisions.

1071
00:58:07,111 --> 00:58:08,680
You know,
personnel for Le Mans.

1072
00:58:08,780 --> 00:58:10,291
Well,
it's a hell of a lineup.

1073
00:58:10,315 --> 00:58:12,050
Ken Miles, Phil Hill,

1074
00:58:12,150 --> 00:58:13,918
Chris Amon, Bruce McLaren.

1075
00:58:14,018 --> 00:58:16,487
Hill's a lock.
Amon, McLaren, too.

1076
00:58:16,588 --> 00:58:18,323
We're less sure about Miles.

1077
00:58:18,423 --> 00:58:19,757
We like Richie Ginther...

1078
00:58:20,158 --> 00:58:22,727
Masten Gregory,
Bob Bondurant.

1079
00:58:23,261 --> 00:58:25,463
Well, you're gonna want
the best driver for the car.

1080
00:58:25,563 --> 00:58:27,165
Understands the machine.

1081
00:58:27,265 --> 00:58:28,566
That's Ken.

1082
00:58:28,666 --> 00:58:30,568
Oh! Yes!

1083
00:58:31,302 --> 00:58:34,772
More of that, please.
More of that, my girl.

1084
00:58:34,872 --> 00:58:37,208
I may not get the finer points
of racing, Mr. Shelby,

1085
00:58:37,308 --> 00:58:38,776
but I do know people.

1086
00:58:39,210 --> 00:58:40,278
Miles is a...

1087
00:58:40,712 --> 00:58:43,348
Well, he's a beatnik.
He dresses like one.

1088
00:58:44,048 --> 00:58:45,483
Ford means reliability.

1089
00:58:46,050 --> 00:58:47,986
Ken Miles is not a Ford man.

1090
00:58:48,086 --> 00:58:49,721
Whoa!

1091
00:58:49,821 --> 00:58:51,856
Giddy-up! Giddy-up!

1092
00:58:54,993 --> 00:58:57,128
What's the lap record
here, Burt?

1093
00:58:57,228 --> 00:58:59,130
1:58.

1094
00:58:59,230 --> 00:59:01,466
- 1:50 dead.
<i>- A beatnik?</i>

1095
00:59:01,566 --> 00:59:04,302
That man landed a busted tank
on the beach at D-Day

1096
00:59:04,402 --> 00:59:06,804
and drove it clean
across Europe to Berlin.

1097
00:59:07,472 --> 00:59:08,873
A beatnik?

1098
00:59:08,973 --> 00:59:10,384
You know, Lee here asked me
a while back,

1099
00:59:10,408 --> 00:59:12,410
"What's the one thing
money can't buy?"

1100
00:59:13,144 --> 00:59:14,445
I'll tell you what it is.

1101
00:59:14,912 --> 00:59:17,115
A pure racer
behind the wheel of your car.

1102
00:59:17,915 --> 00:59:19,417
That's Ken Miles.

1103
00:59:20,985 --> 00:59:22,820
Well, be that as it may...

1104
00:59:23,655 --> 00:59:25,456
we think he may be too pure.

1105
00:59:33,331 --> 00:59:36,901
Carroll, do not lose sight
of the big picture here.

1106
00:59:38,202 --> 00:59:39,404
"Too pure"?

1107
00:59:40,138 --> 00:59:41,973
What exactly does that mean?

1108
00:59:42,607 --> 00:59:44,108
It means
he's all about himself.

1109
00:59:46,010 --> 00:59:47,879
ABC puts a microphone
under his nose,

1110
00:59:47,979 --> 00:59:50,315
perhaps there's a detail
he dislikes,

1111
00:59:50,415 --> 00:59:51,549
millions watching...

1112
00:59:51,649 --> 00:59:53,786
do you trust him not to
put out the wrong message?

1113
00:59:53,885 --> 00:59:55,386
Well, look, you can get
a clean-cut,

1114
00:59:55,486 --> 00:59:56,587
all-American poster boy

1115
00:59:56,688 --> 00:59:57,798
and stick him
behind the wheel,

1116
00:59:57,822 --> 00:59:59,057
teach him what to say.

1117
00:59:59,157 --> 01:00:00,825
Shit, you get Doris Day
to drive the car,

1118
01:00:00,925 --> 01:00:02,160
if all you want to do is lose.

1119
01:00:02,795 --> 01:00:05,830
So, you don't agree with us
on this issue?

1120
01:00:07,899 --> 01:00:10,201
I'm saying you gotta trust me
on this one.

1121
01:00:10,868 --> 01:00:12,112
Carroll,
with marketing concerns,

1122
01:00:12,136 --> 01:00:13,571
that's just not possible.

1123
01:00:15,940 --> 01:00:18,943
Put a Ford-type driver
in a Ford car, Mr. Shelby.

1124
01:00:19,644 --> 01:00:21,179
That's the Ford way.

1125
01:00:27,685 --> 01:00:29,997
<i>Yet another
championship win for Ferrari</i>

1126
01:00:30,021 --> 01:00:31,723
<i>as British driver John Surtees</i>

1127
01:00:31,824 --> 01:00:33,491
<i>pilots his Ferrari 312...</i>

1128
01:00:33,591 --> 01:00:35,193
Ferrari wins.

1129
01:00:35,293 --> 01:00:37,862
<i>It's Surtees'
first win since the '64...</i>

1130
01:00:37,962 --> 01:00:39,765
Wedges. We have wedges.

1131
01:00:39,864 --> 01:00:41,834
Oh, good, good, good.

1132
01:00:41,933 --> 01:00:43,267
Perfect.

1133
01:00:44,068 --> 01:00:46,070
- 40?
- Yep.

1134
01:00:55,079 --> 01:00:56,481
- Hey, boss.
- Hey, Dan.

1135
01:00:56,581 --> 01:00:58,950
- Boss, Ferrari just bagged...
- You got a passport?

1136
01:00:59,050 --> 01:01:00,050
What's that?

1137
01:01:00,084 --> 01:01:01,854
Sign that. Get a passport.

1138
01:01:01,953 --> 01:01:03,721
Get it back to me
by Friday. Frosty.

1139
01:01:03,822 --> 01:01:05,089
Boys, I'm going to France.

1140
01:01:07,258 --> 01:01:08,559
Phil.

1141
01:01:08,659 --> 01:01:10,261
Ken, can I get a word?

1142
01:01:16,667 --> 01:01:17,935
Oh.

1143
01:01:19,036 --> 01:01:20,505
Can I take this?

1144
01:01:20,605 --> 01:01:21,706
Hey.

1145
01:01:22,073 --> 01:01:25,143
Do you know why Ford named it
the GT40?

1146
01:01:25,243 --> 01:01:27,145
Why they put that "40"
on there?

1147
01:01:27,245 --> 01:01:29,180
- No.
- Regulations. All right?

1148
01:01:29,280 --> 01:01:31,850
We gotta be 40 inches high

1149
01:01:31,949 --> 01:01:34,685
to make the ground
clearance requirements.

1150
01:01:34,787 --> 01:01:35,854
No more, no less.

1151
01:01:35,953 --> 01:01:37,355
They measure it
before every race.

1152
01:01:37,455 --> 01:01:40,391
Problem is,
that with that height,

1153
01:01:40,491 --> 01:01:43,561
there's too much drag
under the car, all right?

1154
01:01:43,661 --> 01:01:45,263
So, we have a solution.

1155
01:01:45,363 --> 01:01:47,064
Wedges. We put wedges
in the suspension...

1156
01:01:47,165 --> 01:01:49,033
You're not coming next week.

1157
01:01:51,737 --> 01:01:53,137
You're not coming, Ken.

1158
01:01:56,307 --> 01:01:59,243
We're taking McLaren,
Chris Amon, Phil Hill...

1159
01:02:00,445 --> 01:02:01,712
and Bob Bondurant.

1160
01:02:02,513 --> 01:02:04,148
It's Ford's call.

1161
01:02:05,349 --> 01:02:07,853
It is their opinion that
you are not a good image,

1162
01:02:07,952 --> 01:02:10,254
so you cannot drive
their race car.

1163
01:02:11,556 --> 01:02:13,300
And putting aside the fact
that you made that car

1164
01:02:13,324 --> 01:02:14,692
whatever the hell it is...

1165
01:02:15,393 --> 01:02:18,396
and you're the best man
I got behind the wheel...

1166
01:02:38,149 --> 01:02:40,051
I'm gonna reroute
the oil line.

1167
01:02:40,151 --> 01:02:41,954
If there's spillage,
it could drip

1168
01:02:42,053 --> 01:02:43,789
onto the rear nearside disc.

1169
01:02:43,889 --> 01:02:44,989
Ken...

1170
01:02:45,089 --> 01:02:46,157
Tell the boys

1171
01:02:46,257 --> 01:02:50,328
to watch their pace
come sunrise.

1172
01:02:50,428 --> 01:02:54,131
The, uh,
the gearbox will overheat.

1173
01:03:11,984 --> 01:03:13,184
Ken, the race
is starting soon.

1174
01:03:13,284 --> 01:03:14,753
Want it on the radio?

1175
01:03:14,853 --> 01:03:16,387
Not unless you do.

1176
01:03:35,306 --> 01:03:36,742
<i>...of the race.</i>

1177
01:03:36,842 --> 01:03:37,774
<i>There they are.</i>

1178
01:03:37,776 --> 01:03:39,096
<i>The Maserati going
into the Esses,</i>

1179
01:03:39,143 --> 01:03:40,220
<i>but it's still
the number 2 car,</i>

1180
01:03:40,244 --> 01:03:41,345
<i>driven by Chris Amon.</i>

1181
01:03:41,445 --> 01:03:43,314
<i>In third place
is the number 1 Ford</i>

1182
01:03:43,414 --> 01:03:45,049
<i>that is driven
by Bruce McLaren.</i>

1183
01:03:45,149 --> 01:03:47,485
<i>A tremendously fast start
for the Ford GT.</i>

1184
01:03:47,585 --> 01:03:51,522
<i>3:43.4 lap
for car number 2, a Ford.</i>

1185
01:03:51,622 --> 01:03:53,300
<i>I think
it's a little bit quick</i>

1186
01:03:53,324 --> 01:03:54,458
<i>for this stage of the game.</i>

1187
01:03:54,559 --> 01:03:55,803
<i>Little bit quick right now.</i>

1188
01:03:55,827 --> 01:03:57,194
Racing too hot.

1189
01:03:58,462 --> 01:03:59,673
<i>This could go down</i>

1190
01:03:59,697 --> 01:04:01,241
<i>to the last hour or so,
don't you think?</i>

1191
01:04:01,265 --> 01:04:02,342
<i>It could,
but the probabilities</i>

1192
01:04:02,366 --> 01:04:03,434
<i>for a finish like that</i>

1193
01:04:03,534 --> 01:04:05,603
<i>in a 24-hour race
are awfully small.</i>

1194
01:04:05,703 --> 01:04:07,514
<i>Another Ford
has come into the pits.</i>

1195
01:04:07,538 --> 01:04:09,942
<i>It's being pushed into
the pits by the mechanics.</i>

1196
01:04:10,042 --> 01:04:11,509
Head gasket.

1197
01:04:12,176 --> 01:04:14,378
The car's not a moon rocket.

1198
01:04:14,478 --> 01:04:15,757
<i>Trailing
Bob Bondurant in fourth,</i>

1199
01:04:15,781 --> 01:04:16,815
<i>car number 7.</i>

1200
01:04:16,915 --> 01:04:19,985
<i>Leading number 20, Ferrari.
Michael Parkes.</i>

1201
01:04:20,084 --> 01:04:22,324
<i>So, we have Ford running one,
two, three. How about that?</i>

1202
01:04:22,386 --> 01:04:24,488
Too soon. Surely too soon.

1203
01:04:26,858 --> 01:04:28,860
<i>One has
to really be respectful</i>

1204
01:04:28,961 --> 01:04:30,261
<i>of the mechanism with any...</i>

1205
01:04:42,406 --> 01:04:43,785
<i>Here's the big story,</i>

1206
01:04:43,809 --> 01:04:46,344
<i>the lead Ford, driven
by Richie Ginther, retired</i>

1207
01:04:46,444 --> 01:04:48,479
<i>with gearbox trouble,
and the new leader...</i>

1208
01:04:48,579 --> 01:04:52,350
Gearbox. I told them.
Be gentle with it.

1209
01:04:52,450 --> 01:04:54,127
<i>...and his
partner Lorenzo Bandini...</i>

1210
01:04:54,151 --> 01:04:55,295
<i>...who was one of</i>

1211
01:04:55,319 --> 01:04:57,321
<i>the winning drivers last year.</i>

1212
01:04:58,757 --> 01:05:00,324
Who's there?

1213
01:05:01,592 --> 01:05:02,872
<i>Again, we're back,</i>

1214
01:05:02,928 --> 01:05:05,463
<i>speaking to you live
from Le Mans, France.</i>

1215
01:05:05,563 --> 01:05:08,165
<i>The 24 Hours of Le Mans,
the Grand Prix of Endurance,</i>

1216
01:05:08,265 --> 01:05:09,868
<i>the 33rd renewal.</i>

1217
01:05:10,936 --> 01:05:12,603
What's that
you're listening to?

1218
01:05:13,204 --> 01:05:15,439
Oh, some race over in France.

1219
01:05:18,744 --> 01:05:19,811
Exciting?

1220
01:05:20,411 --> 01:05:22,513
I'm not really paying
much attention.

1221
01:05:22,613 --> 01:05:25,182
<i>However, Phil,
there was one time in 1933,</i>

1222
01:05:25,282 --> 01:05:28,219
<i>when the lead changed hands
three times.</i>

1223
01:05:32,824 --> 01:05:34,392
<i>♪ I ain't lyin' ♪</i>

1224
01:05:36,394 --> 01:05:38,830
<i>♪ No, I ain't lyin' ♪</i>

1225
01:05:40,297 --> 01:05:41,666
It's not exactly champagne...

1226
01:05:41,767 --> 01:05:43,769
<i>♪ You know
I can't stand it... ♪</i>

1227
01:05:45,169 --> 01:05:47,139
...but it's got bubbles.

1228
01:05:47,238 --> 01:05:49,206
<i>♪ You know better, daddy ♪</i>

1229
01:05:50,441 --> 01:05:53,912
<i>♪ I can't stand it
'cause you put me down ♪</i>

1230
01:05:55,013 --> 01:05:56,447
<i>♪ Yeah, yeah ♪</i>

1231
01:05:59,084 --> 01:06:00,518
<i>♪ I put a spell on you ♪</i>

1232
01:06:04,022 --> 01:06:06,758
<i>♪ Because you're mine ♪</i>

1233
01:06:10,294 --> 01:06:11,529
<i>♪ You're mine ♪</i>

1234
01:06:16,134 --> 01:06:17,535
Thanks, Mollie.

1235
01:06:25,811 --> 01:06:27,244
<i>♪ Yeah, yeah ♪</i>

1236
01:06:28,880 --> 01:06:30,548
<i>♪ Oh, yeah ♪</i>

1237
01:06:50,701 --> 01:06:53,471
There's a difference
between Ford and Ferrari...

1238
01:07:02,279 --> 01:07:03,414
Grace.

1239
01:07:11,455 --> 01:07:14,793
Yes, sir.
I will send him right in.

1240
01:07:15,794 --> 01:07:16,962
Thank you.

1241
01:07:19,330 --> 01:07:21,800
Mr. Shelby,
Mr. Ford will see you now.

1242
01:07:22,500 --> 01:07:24,136
- All right.
- Are you still willing

1243
01:07:24,236 --> 01:07:26,437
to stake your reputation
on this guy?

1244
01:07:28,272 --> 01:07:29,808
This way,
Mr. Shelby.

1245
01:07:39,918 --> 01:07:41,285
Mr. Ford.

1246
01:07:41,787 --> 01:07:42,954
Gentlemen.

1247
01:07:43,054 --> 01:07:44,522
Shelby.

1248
01:07:56,902 --> 01:08:00,005
Give me one reason
why I don't fire everyone

1249
01:08:00,105 --> 01:08:01,940
associated with
this abomination

1250
01:08:02,040 --> 01:08:03,440
starting with you.

1251
01:08:09,981 --> 01:08:11,315
Well, sir...

1252
01:08:12,349 --> 01:08:13,869
I was thinking
about that very question

1253
01:08:13,952 --> 01:08:17,055
as I sat out there
in your lovely waiting room.

1254
01:08:18,957 --> 01:08:20,225
As I was sitting there...

1255
01:08:20,759 --> 01:08:23,561
I watched that little
red folder right there...

1256
01:08:24,328 --> 01:08:26,097
go through four pairs
of hands...

1257
01:08:27,431 --> 01:08:28,834
before it got to you.

1258
01:08:29,533 --> 01:08:30,836
'Course that doesn't include...

1259
01:08:31,736 --> 01:08:33,839
the 22 or so
other Ford employees

1260
01:08:33,939 --> 01:08:35,459
who probably poked at it
before it made

1261
01:08:35,539 --> 01:08:37,441
its way up to the 19th floor.

1262
01:08:39,110 --> 01:08:40,678
All due respect, sir,

1263
01:08:41,579 --> 01:08:43,647
you can't win a race
by committee.

1264
01:08:45,083 --> 01:08:46,852
You need one man in charge.

1265
01:08:47,551 --> 01:08:49,921
Now, the good news,
as I see it,

1266
01:08:50,288 --> 01:08:52,057
is that even with
all the extra weight...

1267
01:08:54,326 --> 01:08:56,328
we still managed
to put old Mr. Ferrari

1268
01:08:56,427 --> 01:08:57,863
exactly where we want him.

1269
01:08:59,164 --> 01:09:00,464
Did we?

1270
01:09:00,899 --> 01:09:02,000
Oh, yes.

