01:09:03,869 --> 01:09:05,103
Expand.

1272
01:09:06,403 --> 01:09:07,671
Well...

1273
01:09:09,274 --> 01:09:10,641
sure, we hadn't...

1274
01:09:11,408 --> 01:09:13,677
We haven't worked out
how to corner yet.

1275
01:09:14,511 --> 01:09:15,713
Or stay cool.

1276
01:09:16,480 --> 01:09:18,850
Or stay on the ground.

1277
01:09:19,450 --> 01:09:20,952
And a lot of stuff broke.

1278
01:09:21,685 --> 01:09:24,388
In fact, the only thing that
didn't break was the brakes.

1279
01:09:24,956 --> 01:09:26,791
Hell, right now,
we don't even know

1280
01:09:26,892 --> 01:09:29,761
if our paint job will last
the whole 24 hours.

1281
01:09:35,633 --> 01:09:37,068
But our last lap...

1282
01:09:37,601 --> 01:09:41,339
we clocked 218 miles an hour
down the Mulsanne Straight.

1283
01:09:41,840 --> 01:09:45,277
Now, in all his years
of racing...

1284
01:09:46,011 --> 01:09:49,713
old Enzo ain't never seen
anything move that fast.

1285
01:09:50,949 --> 01:09:52,083
And now he knows...

1286
01:09:52,650 --> 01:09:54,052
without a doubt...

1287
01:09:55,653 --> 01:09:57,688
we're faster than he is...

1288
01:10:00,859 --> 01:10:02,894
even with the wrong driver...

1289
01:10:04,062 --> 01:10:05,562
and all the committees.

1290
01:10:07,299 --> 01:10:08,699
And that's what
he's thinking about

1291
01:10:08,800 --> 01:10:11,202
while he's sitting
in Modena, Italy...

1292
01:10:12,170 --> 01:10:13,738
right now.

1293
01:10:15,173 --> 01:10:16,875
That man is scared to death...

1294
01:10:18,009 --> 01:10:20,912
that this year you actually
might be smart enough

1295
01:10:21,012 --> 01:10:22,479
to start trusting me.

1296
01:10:25,449 --> 01:10:26,851
So, yeah...

1297
01:10:28,619 --> 01:10:31,522
I'd say you got Ferrari
exactly where you want him.

1298
01:10:35,226 --> 01:10:36,560
You're welcome.

1299
01:10:54,245 --> 01:10:55,713
Come here.

1300
01:11:03,288 --> 01:11:05,090
See that little building
down there?

1301
01:11:05,723 --> 01:11:07,092
In World War II...

1302
01:11:07,591 --> 01:11:11,730
three out of five US bombers
rolled off that line.

1303
01:11:13,898 --> 01:11:16,001
You think
Roosevelt beat Hitler?

1304
01:11:17,634 --> 01:11:18,634
Think again.

1305
01:11:18,669 --> 01:11:19,771
This isn't the first time

1306
01:11:19,871 --> 01:11:22,107
Ford Motor's gone
to war in Europe.

1307
01:11:24,541 --> 01:11:27,078
We know how to do more
than push paper.

1308
01:11:29,546 --> 01:11:32,017
And there is one man
running this company.

1309
01:11:34,452 --> 01:11:35,887
You report to him.

1310
01:11:37,288 --> 01:11:38,722
You understand me?

1311
01:11:39,224 --> 01:11:40,624
Yes, sir.

1312
01:11:41,525 --> 01:11:44,062
Go ahead, Carroll.
Go to war.

1313
01:11:47,132 --> 01:11:48,199
Thank you, sir.

1314
01:12:21,132 --> 01:12:22,167
You were right.

1315
01:12:22,734 --> 01:12:24,102
It's the gearbox.

1316
01:12:24,769 --> 01:12:26,104
We ran too hot.

1317
01:12:27,372 --> 01:12:28,740
Three out of four
of 'em broke.

1318
01:12:29,541 --> 01:12:31,042
The rod blew on the other one.

1319
01:12:36,181 --> 01:12:37,849
We're going back, Ken.

1320
01:12:41,386 --> 01:12:44,923
They told me I had
"carte blanche" this time.

1321
01:12:46,324 --> 01:12:48,760
I looked it up.
It's French for "horseshit."

1322
01:12:49,227 --> 01:12:51,563
I know they're gonna squeeze
our nuts any way they can

1323
01:12:51,662 --> 01:12:53,064
soon as they work out how.

1324
01:12:53,597 --> 01:12:55,033
Well, the, uh...

1325
01:12:55,900 --> 01:12:57,268
ice cream's melting.

1326
01:13:00,305 --> 01:13:01,873
All right. Hey, Ken.

1327
01:13:03,408 --> 01:13:05,009
You want me to apologize?

1328
01:13:06,511 --> 01:13:07,779
Mmm.

1329
01:13:08,179 --> 01:13:09,214
You want me to beg?

1330
01:13:09,680 --> 01:13:11,416
I don't know.
Let's try it out.

1331
01:13:11,516 --> 01:13:13,885
Let's, uh, see how that feels.

1332
01:13:20,125 --> 01:13:21,259
Ken, I'm sorry.

1333
01:13:22,560 --> 01:13:23,995
Sincerely.

1334
01:13:25,530 --> 01:13:26,865
Mmm.

1335
01:13:27,866 --> 01:13:30,401
Do you have any idea the kind
of shit that I had to eat

1336
01:13:30,502 --> 01:13:32,070
just to get four wheels
on that grid?

1337
01:13:32,170 --> 01:13:33,171
No, you don't.

1338
01:13:33,271 --> 01:13:35,015
'Cause you don't deal
with any of that stuff.

1339
01:13:35,039 --> 01:13:36,908
Now knock it off, Ken.
We got work to do,

1340
01:13:37,008 --> 01:13:38,488
and this car ain't gonna
build itself.

1341
01:13:47,684 --> 01:13:50,721
Okay. All right.

1342
01:13:59,464 --> 01:14:02,000
God.

1343
01:14:02,500 --> 01:14:03,768
Come here.

1344
01:14:04,736 --> 01:14:07,005
- Bloody car salesman.
- Shit!

1345
01:14:09,941 --> 01:14:11,708
Come on.
Now you're gonna get it.

1346
01:14:16,347 --> 01:14:17,448
Get off me!

1347
01:14:19,918 --> 01:14:23,421
Stubborn son of a bitch.

1348
01:14:23,521 --> 01:14:24,923
God!

1349
01:14:27,091 --> 01:14:28,726
- You just look...
- Right.

1350
01:14:29,561 --> 01:14:30,862
- Yeah, now.
- You...

1351
01:14:30,962 --> 01:14:32,530
- Ow!
- You all right?

1352
01:14:32,630 --> 01:14:34,065
Shit!

1353
01:14:35,533 --> 01:14:37,101
Now you're gonna get it.

1354
01:14:38,702 --> 01:14:40,538
Come here.

1355
01:14:43,174 --> 01:14:44,209
Done.

1356
01:14:49,380 --> 01:14:50,481
Mollie, darling.

1357
01:14:51,282 --> 01:14:52,350
Yes, love?

1358
01:14:52,716 --> 01:14:54,285
Can I get a fizzy pop, please?

1359
01:14:55,587 --> 01:14:56,854
Yes, love.

1360
01:14:58,489 --> 01:14:59,791
You want one, too, Shelby?

1361
01:15:00,158 --> 01:15:02,260
- No. No.
- Uh, yes, please, Mollie.

1362
01:15:02,360 --> 01:15:04,229
No. He can get his own.

1363
01:15:04,596 --> 01:15:06,030
Just for me, please.

1364
01:15:12,770 --> 01:15:14,138
How long has that been?

1365
01:15:15,073 --> 01:15:17,141
Oh, it's gotta be three
or four years, at least.

1366
01:15:17,242 --> 01:15:19,210
Right. Riverside.

1367
01:15:19,310 --> 01:15:22,280
Yeah.
SCCA Divisional Championship.

1368
01:15:22,747 --> 01:15:24,115
You broke my finger.

1369
01:15:25,950 --> 01:15:29,854
What's that nippy bloody thing

1370
01:15:30,188 --> 01:15:31,723
you do under the arm,
that thing?

1371
01:15:31,823 --> 01:15:33,524
Yeah. I call that
the Llama Bite.

1372
01:15:33,625 --> 01:15:36,094
You name it?

1373
01:15:36,194 --> 01:15:38,463
Where'd you learn that?
The Girl Scouts?

1374
01:15:38,563 --> 01:15:41,065
- What? You wanna go again?
- Here you go.

1375
01:15:42,333 --> 01:15:43,401
You're an angel.

1376
01:15:43,501 --> 01:15:44,535
Thank you.

1377
01:15:44,636 --> 01:15:45,770
My pleasure.

1378
01:15:46,571 --> 01:15:49,107
Right. Well, I'm about to go
to the grocery store.

1379
01:15:49,207 --> 01:15:51,075
Anything you think
you'll need?

1380
01:15:51,643 --> 01:15:53,811
Um, ice cream.

1381
01:15:54,679 --> 01:15:56,481
Ice cream would be good
and, uh...

1382
01:15:57,348 --> 01:15:58,416
bread.

1383
01:15:59,617 --> 01:16:00,718
Right.

1384
01:16:00,852 --> 01:16:02,453
No, I'm good.
Thank you.

1385
01:16:03,154 --> 01:16:05,223
Thanks, Moll.

1386
01:16:05,323 --> 01:16:06,958
You still take those
for your ticker?

1387
01:16:07,392 --> 01:16:09,560
Only 'cause
they're so delicious.

1388
01:16:09,661 --> 01:16:12,797
- Up yours.
- Oh, go to hell.

1389
01:16:20,438 --> 01:16:22,607
Come on.
Giddy-up. Giddy-up. Giddy-up.

1390
01:16:38,423 --> 01:16:41,225
Phil! Here's the one
for you, mate.

1391
01:16:41,326 --> 01:16:42,593
Dino, come here.

1392
01:17:00,878 --> 01:17:02,046
Well?

1393
01:17:02,146 --> 01:17:03,715
There's still lag
when I hit the gas.

1394
01:17:03,816 --> 01:17:05,259
Let's get rid of
the vacuum secondaries.

1395
01:17:05,283 --> 01:17:06,752
Charlie, get a Holley carb.

1396
01:17:06,851 --> 01:17:08,653
We're gonna rebuild
the throttle assembly.

1397
01:17:08,754 --> 01:17:10,154
Three weeks to Daytona,

1398
01:17:10,188 --> 01:17:13,057
and it still feels
like a bag of squirrels.

1399
01:17:13,157 --> 01:17:14,425
Brake heat.

1400
01:17:14,859 --> 01:17:16,494
That's a whole different
ball game.

1401
01:17:16,594 --> 01:17:19,197
All right, Petey,
let's go for that ride.

1402
01:17:27,840 --> 01:17:29,173
What are you doing?

1403
01:17:30,708 --> 01:17:32,043
You see that crack?

1404
01:17:32,143 --> 01:17:34,011
That's my marker
for turn eight.

1405
01:17:36,881 --> 01:17:38,349
What, to slow down?

1406
01:17:39,183 --> 01:17:42,387
Uh, brush the brakes
and downshift.

1407
01:17:44,288 --> 01:17:46,924
But you'll be going
150 miles an hour.

1408
01:17:47,658 --> 01:17:48,794
Yeah.

1409
01:17:48,893 --> 01:17:50,428
So how do you see it?

1410
01:17:50,528 --> 01:17:53,564
You're going fast,
but as the car speeds up...

1411
01:17:54,098 --> 01:17:56,467
everything else slows down.

1412
01:17:56,567 --> 01:17:58,236
You don't do that.

1413
01:17:59,036 --> 01:18:00,938
You do this. Right?

1414
01:18:01,038 --> 01:18:03,040
And then you see everything.

1415
01:18:05,676 --> 01:18:07,478
Do you set other markers?

1416
01:18:07,578 --> 01:18:09,914
Indeed I do.

1417
01:18:11,416 --> 01:18:12,583
Lots of them.

1418
01:18:14,452 --> 01:18:16,789
Yeah, 'cause
you can't just push

1419
01:18:16,889 --> 01:18:18,857
the car hard
the whole way, right?

1420
01:18:18,956 --> 01:18:21,492
That's right. You have
to be kind to the car.

1421
01:18:21,592 --> 01:18:25,963
You feel the poor thing
groaning underneath you.

1422
01:18:26,732 --> 01:18:30,803
If you're gonna push a piece
of machinery to the limit

1423
01:18:30,903 --> 01:18:32,470
and expect it
to hold together,

1424
01:18:32,570 --> 01:18:37,141
you have to have some sense
of where that limit is.

1425
01:18:39,845 --> 01:18:41,078
Look out there.

1426
01:18:41,979 --> 01:18:45,149
Out there is the perfect lap.

1427
01:18:47,385 --> 01:18:48,553
No mistakes.

1428
01:18:49,187 --> 01:18:51,556
Every gear change,
every corner...

1429
01:18:53,324 --> 01:18:54,392
perfect.

1430
01:18:55,894 --> 01:18:57,261
You see it?

1431
01:19:01,399 --> 01:19:02,567
I think so.

1432
01:19:04,569 --> 01:19:06,137
Most people can't.

1433
01:19:07,271 --> 01:19:10,241
Most people don't even know
it's out there, but it is.

1434
01:19:12,510 --> 01:19:13,678
It's there.

1435
01:19:16,714 --> 01:19:18,182
You want some ice cream?

1436
01:19:20,718 --> 01:19:22,153
- Yeah.
- All right.

1437
01:19:22,987 --> 01:19:24,255
Come on, then.

1438
01:19:24,790 --> 01:19:26,157
Do you know
what this marker is?

1439
01:19:26,257 --> 01:19:27,367
- What?
- That one.

1440
01:19:27,391 --> 01:19:28,861
Pull my finger.
You'll find out.

1441
01:19:51,048 --> 01:19:53,084
How much longer
before he comes in?

1442
01:19:53,184 --> 01:19:55,553
Uh, well, we change drivers
every four hours,

1443
01:19:55,653 --> 01:19:57,431
- so about 10 minutes.
<i>- No, hang on.</i>

1444
01:19:57,455 --> 01:20:00,057
You're saying Beebe
is 100 percent in charge now?

1445
01:20:00,157 --> 01:20:02,293
<i>Yes,
and he wants Miles gone.</i>

1446
01:20:02,895 --> 01:20:04,595
Look, it's personal
with this guy.

1447
01:20:04,695 --> 01:20:06,664
And, yes, he has the leverage
to stick it to you.

1448
01:20:06,765 --> 01:20:08,666
<i>He and the Deuce
are flying there tomorrow.</i>

1449
01:20:08,767 --> 01:20:09,878
He's gonna tell you in person.

1450
01:20:09,902 --> 01:20:11,068
Now, all he is hoping for

1451
01:20:11,168 --> 01:20:12,771
- is that you lose your cool.
- <i>Uh-huh.</i>

1452
01:20:12,871 --> 01:20:14,338
<i>It's time to let this go.</i>

1453
01:20:14,438 --> 01:20:15,841
You cannot destroy
the whole thing.

1454
01:20:15,941 --> 01:20:16,975
Not for one goddamn guy.

1455
01:20:17,074 --> 01:20:19,011
- Sure, I can.
- <i>Well, why?</i>

1456
01:20:19,110 --> 01:20:20,320
'Cause while
we're here talking,

1457
01:20:20,344 --> 01:20:21,679
he's out there
getting it done.

1458
01:20:29,220 --> 01:20:31,222
Oh, shit!

1459
01:20:32,858 --> 01:20:34,458
He's got brake fade.

1460
01:20:41,833 --> 01:20:43,067
Ease off!

1461
01:20:53,177 --> 01:20:54,178
<i>Carroll?</i>

1462
01:20:54,445 --> 01:20:55,757
- Get him out!
- Peter!

1463
01:20:55,781 --> 01:20:57,582
Go on. Go inside.

1464
01:20:57,682 --> 01:20:58,581
Just stay there.

1465
01:20:58,583 --> 01:21:00,052
- Get Ken!
- Ken!

1466
01:21:00,151 --> 01:21:01,552
Get him out!

1467
01:21:03,254 --> 01:21:04,422
There he is!

1468
01:21:04,522 --> 01:21:05,354
Ken!

1469
01:21:05,356 --> 01:21:06,724
I can see him.

1470
01:21:13,097 --> 01:21:14,498
- Ken!
- Come on.

1471
01:21:21,105 --> 01:21:22,406
The brakes.

1472
01:21:31,716 --> 01:21:34,619
Let's just rip out
the damn engine. All right?

1473
01:21:34,719 --> 01:21:37,421
We can't use it
if we can't stop.

1474
01:21:37,521 --> 01:21:38,933
You know,
the brakes would last longer

1475
01:21:38,957 --> 01:21:40,591
if we slowed down a bit.

1476
01:21:40,859 --> 01:21:43,527
Wouldn't that defeat the whole
purpose of the extra power?

1477
01:21:44,195 --> 01:21:45,372
You know,
I thought the whole point

1478
01:21:45,396 --> 01:21:46,765
was to win the damned race.

1479
01:21:47,498 --> 01:21:49,533
Maybe we could design
a new assembly.

1480
01:21:49,634 --> 01:21:53,337
Instead of swapping out
the pads in the pits...

1481
01:21:53,739 --> 01:21:56,574
swap out
the entire braking system.

1482
01:21:56,674 --> 01:21:58,209
Rotors included.

1483
01:21:58,777 --> 01:21:59,911
Put in a fresh one.

1484
01:22:00,012 --> 01:22:01,780
Wait, wait, wait, Pops,

1485
01:22:01,880 --> 01:22:02,981
are we allowed to do that?

1486
01:22:03,081 --> 01:22:06,283
I don't know.
I don't read French.

1487
01:22:07,819 --> 01:22:12,758
Well, brakes are "a part"
like any other, right?

1488
01:22:12,858 --> 01:22:15,192
We are allowed
to change parts.

1489
01:22:15,292 --> 01:22:17,161
Yes.
Will we have time to do that?

1490
01:22:17,261 --> 01:22:18,864
I don't know yet,
Charlie.

1491
01:22:19,463 --> 01:22:21,066
I'm gonna take him home.

1492
01:22:21,165 --> 01:22:22,266
All right.

1493
01:22:22,366 --> 01:22:23,601
Sort this shit out.

1494
01:22:23,701 --> 01:22:24,770
I will.

1495
01:22:34,211 --> 01:22:36,614
Have you ever been on fire?

1496
01:22:38,750 --> 01:22:42,520
Uh, well, no,
it's never happened to me.

1497
01:22:47,391 --> 01:22:49,861
But the suit's
flameproof, see?

1498
01:22:49,961 --> 01:22:51,529
It, uh, keeps heat out.

1499
01:22:52,496 --> 01:22:53,531
Yeah.

1500
01:22:55,133 --> 01:22:57,501
But Lewis-Evans
burned to death

1501
01:22:57,601 --> 01:22:58,837
in the Moroccan Grand Prix.

1502
01:22:58,937 --> 01:23:00,939
He had a flameproof suit on.

1503
01:23:02,174 --> 01:23:05,209
Mm-hmm. Yeah, but, um...

1504
01:23:08,013 --> 01:23:09,313
See, he got stuck.

1505
01:23:09,413 --> 01:23:10,882
He couldn't breathe.

1506
01:23:11,950 --> 01:23:15,553
So, as long as you get out
of the car, you're okay.

1507
01:23:19,724 --> 01:23:21,325
Dad got out.

1508
01:23:22,426 --> 01:23:24,261
- He sure did.
- Peter!

1509
01:23:28,100 --> 01:23:29,400
Bye.

1510
01:23:30,234 --> 01:23:31,569
See ya.

1511
01:23:34,172 --> 01:23:35,774
- You all right?
- Yeah.

1512
01:23:36,975 --> 01:23:38,309
What's wrong with you?

1513
01:23:39,177 --> 01:23:40,411
And don't be telling me brakes

1514
01:23:40,511 --> 01:23:42,748
or me almost kicking
the bucket out there.

1515
01:23:42,848 --> 01:23:45,382
It's something to do
with the suits, isn't it?

1516
01:23:47,786 --> 01:23:49,154
It's under control.

1517
01:23:49,253 --> 01:23:50,588
What is it?

1518
01:23:50,688 --> 01:23:52,299
You know how we talked about
how you do your thing,

1519
01:23:52,323 --> 01:23:53,390
I do my thing?

1520
01:23:53,491 --> 01:23:54,931
- This is my thing.
- Really, Shel...

1521
01:23:54,993 --> 01:23:56,460
Just trust me, Ken.

1522
01:23:57,129 --> 01:23:58,496
You got a plan?

1523
01:23:59,197 --> 01:24:00,498
Absolutely.

1524
01:24:00,999 --> 01:24:02,033
It a good one?

1525
01:24:03,001 --> 01:24:04,268
It's high risk.

1526
01:24:04,368 --> 01:24:05,402
How high risk?

1527
01:24:05,503 --> 01:24:07,005
Extremely high risk.

1528
01:24:08,940 --> 01:24:10,374
Well, that's something.

1529
01:24:11,109 --> 01:24:13,011
- Glad we had this talk.
- Anytime.

1530
01:24:25,257 --> 01:24:27,726
Mr. Ford, this is a surprise.

1531
01:24:28,526 --> 01:24:30,796
Apologies for the unannounced
intrusion, Mr. Shelby,

1532
01:24:30,896 --> 01:24:34,298
but when a man pays $9 million
for an automobile,

1533
01:24:34,398 --> 01:24:36,234
he ought to at least
be able to see it.

1534
01:24:36,333 --> 01:24:37,903
Well, that sounds
reasonable enough.

1535
01:24:38,003 --> 01:24:39,838
Uh, Shelby, could I have a word?

1536
01:24:39,938 --> 01:24:41,106
Sure.

1537
01:24:41,206 --> 01:24:43,008
- In private?
- Uh, yeah.

1538
01:24:43,108 --> 01:24:44,508
That would be preferable.

1539
01:24:44,608 --> 01:24:45,768
All right.
Hey, Phil.

1540
01:24:45,844 --> 01:24:47,478
You wanna take care
of Mr. Ford here?

1541
01:24:47,578 --> 01:24:49,247
Mr. Ford,
that's Phil Remington.

1542
01:24:49,346 --> 01:24:50,414
Of course.

1543
01:24:50,514 --> 01:24:51,658
Come up
to my office, Leo.

1544
01:24:51,682 --> 01:24:52,827
- Pleasure to meet you, sir.
- Phil.

1545
01:24:52,851 --> 01:24:54,953
Give you a little tour
of your car.

1546
01:24:55,787 --> 01:24:58,857
We, uh, took out
your 289 small block...

1547
01:24:59,423 --> 01:25:01,893
and put in a 4277-liter.

1548
01:25:04,528 --> 01:25:06,832
Uh, firstly,
I want to just clear the air.

1549
01:25:06,932 --> 01:25:09,301
I hope
that whatever disagreements

1550
01:25:09,400 --> 01:25:11,303
between us
can just be chalked up...

1551
01:25:11,870 --> 01:25:14,538
to natural red-bloodedness
in the heat of battle.

1552
01:25:14,638 --> 01:25:17,575
Oh, I appreciate that, Leo.
Truly, I do.

1553
01:25:18,944 --> 01:25:21,947
It falls on me, Shelby,
to inform you

1554
01:25:22,047 --> 01:25:23,547
that I have been appointed

1555
01:25:23,647 --> 01:25:26,684
overall executive director
of the racing program.

1556
01:25:27,919 --> 01:25:31,756
Now, I do hope that this
won't be a problem between us.

1557
01:25:32,556 --> 01:25:34,826
Well, I assure you, Leo,
it will not.

1558
01:25:45,103 --> 01:25:46,403
Hey, Carroll...

1559
01:25:46,872 --> 01:25:47,738
Carroll!

1560
01:25:47,740 --> 01:25:49,074
And what is that top speed

1561
01:25:49,174 --> 01:25:50,308
with the, uh, 427?

1562
01:25:50,407 --> 01:25:52,177
Well, why don't we take it
for a spin?

1563
01:25:52,277 --> 01:25:53,644
- What?
- Yeah, go on, Mr. Ford.

1564
01:25:53,745 --> 01:25:56,014
- Hop on in. Go on.
- You want me to...

1565
01:25:56,114 --> 01:25:58,316
Just see
what $9 million feels like.

1566
01:25:58,415 --> 01:26:00,852
Hey!

1567
01:26:00,952 --> 01:26:02,153
God...

1568
01:26:05,857 --> 01:26:06,892
Open the door!

1569
01:26:06,992 --> 01:26:08,659
Hey, open the door!

1570
01:26:09,160 --> 01:26:10,962
Open the door!

1571
01:26:13,164 --> 01:26:14,431
Just hold me right there,

1572
01:26:14,531 --> 01:26:16,034
and you take my hand.

1573
01:26:17,668 --> 01:26:20,338
Oh, God. I sat on my nuts.

1574
01:26:20,437 --> 01:26:22,797
We're gonna build the next one
for comfort. Don't you worry.

1575
01:26:31,383 --> 01:26:32,716
Open the door.

1576
01:26:32,817 --> 01:26:34,328
Sorry, sir,
if you just give me a moment.

1577
01:26:34,352 --> 01:26:35,495
- Open the door.
- It's a sticky one.

1578
01:26:35,519 --> 01:26:37,055
You ready?

1579
01:26:37,155 --> 01:26:38,900
The name on the middle
of that steering wheel

1580
01:26:38,924 --> 01:26:41,359
should tell you that I was
born ready, Shelby. Hit it.

1581
01:26:41,458 --> 01:26:43,527
Attaboy.

1582
01:26:45,663 --> 01:26:48,532
Whoa! It's got a little kick,
doesn't it?

1583
01:26:48,833 --> 01:26:50,735
- Open this door.
- Oh, there we go.

1584
01:26:50,835 --> 01:26:53,104
Good God, Mr. Beebe.
You okay, sir?

1585
01:26:54,940 --> 01:26:57,541
Whoa! Oh, my God!

1586
01:26:58,509 --> 01:27:01,212
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

1587
01:27:05,016 --> 01:27:06,384
Yeah, baby.

1588
01:27:06,483 --> 01:27:09,154
Yeah, baby.

1589
01:27:12,057 --> 01:27:14,225
It's about right now
the uninitiated

1590
01:27:14,326 --> 01:27:16,527
have a tendency
to soil themselves.

1591
01:27:23,534 --> 01:27:26,271
Oh, my God! Whoa!

1592
01:28:02,907 --> 01:28:04,042
Mr. Ford...

1593
01:28:07,979 --> 01:28:09,314
You okay?

1594
01:28:12,649 --> 01:28:13,918
Mr. Ford...

1595
01:28:14,486 --> 01:28:15,586
you all right?

1596
01:28:15,686 --> 01:28:17,088
I had no idea.

1597
01:28:19,590 --> 01:28:21,092
I had no idea.

1598
01:28:24,062 --> 01:28:25,397
I wish my daddy...

1599
01:28:25,764 --> 01:28:27,465
he were alive to see this.

1600
01:28:27,732 --> 01:28:30,601
To feel this.

1601
01:28:32,103 --> 01:28:34,205
Now, this is not a machine
just anybody can get in

1602
01:28:34,305 --> 01:28:35,440
and easily control.

1603
01:28:35,539 --> 01:28:36,975
Absolutely not.

1604
01:28:37,608 --> 01:28:38,642
I had no idea.

1605
01:28:38,743 --> 01:28:40,178
Now, you wanna win Le Mans.

1606
01:28:40,912 --> 01:28:42,414
If you really wanna take
first place,

1607
01:28:42,514 --> 01:28:44,082
Ken Miles is the man to do it.

1608
01:28:53,258 --> 01:28:54,492
Good timing.

1609
01:28:54,591 --> 01:28:55,703
<i>Now, he knows this car</i>

1610
01:28:55,727 --> 01:28:57,328
because he helped me build it.

1611
01:28:58,730 --> 01:29:01,099
Shelby, you know I've already

1612
01:29:01,199 --> 01:29:02,967
appointed Leo Beebe
director of racing.

1613
01:29:03,068 --> 01:29:05,170
Which is exactly
why I'm talking to you.

1614
01:29:06,071 --> 01:29:08,973
Now, you let Ken Miles
race Daytona.

1615
01:29:09,573 --> 01:29:11,042
If he wins...

1616
01:29:11,843 --> 01:29:13,745
he gets to drive Le Mans.

1617
01:29:16,247 --> 01:29:17,449
And if he doesn't?

1618
01:29:18,216 --> 01:29:20,552
Ford Motor Company
gets full ownership

1619
01:29:20,651 --> 01:29:22,053
of Shelby American.

1620
01:29:22,153 --> 01:29:23,488
Lock, stock, and brand.

1621
01:29:23,587 --> 01:29:24,856
Forever.

1622
01:29:27,926 --> 01:29:30,694
<i>We're in
hour six at the Daytona 24,</i>

1623
01:29:30,795 --> 01:29:33,965
<i>and Fords are dominating
the leaderboard.</i>

1624
01:29:34,065 --> 01:29:37,102
<i>Shelby American's Ken Miles
holds a narrow lead</i>

1625
01:29:37,202 --> 01:29:40,271
<i>over the Holman-Moody Ford
driven by Walt Hansgen.</i>

1626
01:29:41,339 --> 01:29:43,707
I don't bloody think so, Walt.

1627
01:30:01,993 --> 01:30:05,196
Oh, this race is not just
a test of our cars,

1628
01:30:05,296 --> 01:30:06,630
but also our teams.

1629
01:30:06,731 --> 01:30:08,731
As you know, we have
a second team out there today.

1630
01:30:08,766 --> 01:30:10,935
- Holman-Moody.
- That's right.

1631
01:30:11,035 --> 01:30:12,604
<i>Number 95, Hansgen,</i>

1632
01:30:12,703 --> 01:30:14,048
<i>blisters through
the front tri-oval</i>

1633
01:30:14,072 --> 01:30:16,241
<i>while closing in on Ken Miles.</i>

1634
01:30:16,341 --> 01:30:17,641
Walt's pushing her too fast.

1635
01:30:17,742 --> 01:30:19,944
He's pushing 7,000 RPM.

1636
01:30:20,044 --> 01:30:21,546
Hey, get the EZ sign
out there.

1637
01:30:21,645 --> 01:30:23,214
Come on. Move. Do it now.

1638
01:30:23,314 --> 01:30:25,383
Every one of these GTs
out there today

1639
01:30:25,483 --> 01:30:27,085
is under
my direct supervision.

1640
01:30:27,185 --> 01:30:30,188
And of course the supervision
of Henry Ford II.

1641
01:30:30,288 --> 01:30:33,358
The drivers,
the speed, the strategy...

1642
01:30:33,791 --> 01:30:36,628
even the RPMs
are determined by us.

1643
01:30:40,331 --> 01:30:42,042
<i>Ken Miles
is locked in a pitched battle</i>

1644
01:30:42,066 --> 01:30:45,203
<i>with Hansgen
as they pass the grandstand.</i>

1645
01:30:48,206 --> 01:30:51,242
<i>Hansgen is taking a run
at Miles entering turn one.</i>

1646
01:30:51,342 --> 01:30:52,544
<i>Miles is boxed in.</i>

1647
01:30:52,644 --> 01:30:54,946
<i>Hansgen slips by
and takes the lead</i>

1648
01:30:55,046 --> 01:30:57,081
<i>approaching
the infield chicane.</i>

1649
01:31:06,791 --> 01:31:07,859
Cor blimey!

1650
01:31:07,959 --> 01:31:09,527
Did you see that?

1651
01:31:09,627 --> 01:31:11,067
<i>The caution flag is out.</i>

1652
01:31:17,302 --> 01:31:19,904
Still racing.
Hey, we are still racing.

1653
01:31:20,004 --> 01:31:21,172
Come on, guys, let's go!

1654
01:31:21,272 --> 01:31:22,272
Let's go. Move it.

1655
01:31:22,340 --> 01:31:23,341
He's coming in.

1656
01:31:24,142 --> 01:31:26,411
Let's go,
let's go, guys. Come on.

1657
01:31:26,511 --> 01:31:27,879
Go, tires up.

1658
01:31:27,979 --> 01:31:29,623
Here, right here.
Let's go. Let's go. Move it.

1659
01:31:29,647 --> 01:31:31,392
- Fuel flying in.
- Breaker bar!

1660
01:31:31,416 --> 01:31:33,218
- We're good.
- It all checked out.

1661
01:31:33,318 --> 01:31:34,852
- 36. 38.
- Go! Go!

1662
01:31:34,953 --> 01:31:37,255
Hansgen is right up our arse.

1663
01:31:37,355 --> 01:31:39,133
If I can just get
outta the pit ahead of him...

1664
01:31:39,157 --> 01:31:41,826
She's running hot,
but I think she'll hold.

1665
01:31:41,926 --> 01:31:43,537
- Fuel's low.
- Bring up the scoop.

1666
01:31:43,561 --> 01:31:44,862
She's hot.

1667
01:31:46,965 --> 01:31:48,833
Hey there, Walt.
Good to see you.

1668
01:31:48,933 --> 01:31:50,635
Yeah, after I get out
of this pit, Shelby,

1669
01:31:50,735 --> 01:31:51,855
it's the last time you will.

1670
01:31:51,936 --> 01:31:52,936
Oh, don't worry.

1671
01:31:53,004 --> 01:31:54,339
We got rearview mirrors.

1672
01:31:55,740 --> 01:31:57,508
What happened
to that Mustang he took out?

1673
01:31:58,276 --> 01:31:59,611
Don't know yet.

1674
01:31:59,711 --> 01:32:02,513
I can push her harder
than six, Shel.

1675
01:32:02,614 --> 01:32:05,016
- I can feel it.
- Uh-huh.

1676
01:32:08,386 --> 01:32:12,257
Hey, how come these guys pit
so much faster than we do?

1677
01:32:12,357 --> 01:32:15,960
They got a goddamn
NASCAR crew, that's why.

1678
01:32:16,060 --> 01:32:18,029
- No shit?
- No shit.

1679
01:32:18,496 --> 01:32:20,298
Go! Go, come on.

1680
01:32:21,633 --> 01:32:23,368
We're clear, we're clear.

1681
01:32:23,468 --> 01:32:24,569
Goddamn NASCAR crew.

1682
01:32:24,669 --> 01:32:26,337
Go, go, go!

1683
01:32:26,739 --> 01:32:28,373
Guys, they've already left.

1684
01:32:31,242 --> 01:32:32,208
Hello?

1685
01:32:32,210 --> 01:32:34,345
<i>There's my Mollie. Hello.</i>

1686
01:32:34,879 --> 01:32:35,947
Hiya, love.

1687
01:32:36,047 --> 01:32:37,882
- Mom? Mom?
- <i>What are you doing?</i>

1688
01:32:37,982 --> 01:32:38,983
Just having a cuppa.

1689
01:32:39,083 --> 01:32:40,753
Mom, ask him about the brakes.

1690
01:32:40,852 --> 01:32:43,254
- Go to bed. It's 1:00 a.m.
- Ask him.

1691
01:32:43,354 --> 01:32:44,689
Go to bed. Now.

1692
01:32:44,789 --> 01:32:46,591
I take it he's not asleep.

1693
01:32:46,691 --> 01:32:48,459
I'm sure he smuggled
in a radio.

1694
01:32:48,559 --> 01:32:49,827
<i>Yeah.</i>

1695
01:32:49,927 --> 01:32:51,205
He said to ask,
"How are the brakes?"

1696
01:32:51,229 --> 01:32:53,064
The brakes? Yes. No, no, no.

1697
01:32:53,164 --> 01:32:55,199
Tell him
they're working for now.

1698
01:32:55,300 --> 01:32:58,002
<i>You know, Shelby's been acting
very strange.</i>

1699
01:32:58,102 --> 01:32:59,170
- <i>Ford have gone...</i>
- Ken.

1700
01:32:59,270 --> 01:33:00,605
<i>...and put up another team.</i>

1701
01:33:00,705 --> 01:33:01,973
- With a GT.
- <i>Ken.</i>

1702
01:33:02,073 --> 01:33:03,274
Some sort of yampy,

1703
01:33:03,374 --> 01:33:05,310
<i>bloody corporate test
or something.</i>

1704
01:33:05,410 --> 01:33:07,412
Just take a rest
whenever you get a chance.

1705
01:33:07,512 --> 01:33:08,952
<i>Sorry, my love,
what were you saying?</i>

1706
01:33:09,047 --> 01:33:10,548
You've only got a few hours.

1707
01:33:10,648 --> 01:33:11,750
<i>I can't hear you very well.</i>

1708
01:33:11,849 --> 01:33:13,217
<i>I'm sorry. I can't hear you.</i>

1709
01:33:13,318 --> 01:33:14,318
<i>Wish me luck.</i>

1710
01:33:14,352 --> 01:33:16,554
- Good luck.
- <i>I love you, darling.</i>

1711
01:33:16,654 --> 01:33:18,990
<i>After 23 hours
here at Daytona,</i>

1712
01:33:19,090 --> 01:33:21,526
<i>Walt Hansgen driving
the green and white Ford</i>

1713
01:33:21,626 --> 01:33:22,894
<i>has a commanding lead</i>

1714
01:33:22,994 --> 01:33:25,330
<i>over Ken Miles
and Shelby American</i>

1715
01:33:25,430 --> 01:33:28,433
<i>as the rest of the field
has fallen off the pace.</i>

1716
01:33:28,533 --> 01:33:29,567
We're locked out.

1717
01:33:29,667 --> 01:33:31,035
Ain't nothing Miles can do

1718
01:33:31,135 --> 01:33:32,603
this late in the race.

1719
01:33:33,137 --> 01:33:35,673
Engine's hot. We gotta keep it
under six thou.

1720
01:34:23,488 --> 01:34:25,156
All right.

1721
01:34:50,181 --> 01:34:51,949
She could come apart.

1722
01:34:52,049 --> 01:34:53,584
One way to find out.

1723
01:34:56,454 --> 01:34:58,990
I thought we were keeping him
under 6,000?

1724
01:34:59,390 --> 01:35:00,925
Shut up, Don.

1725
01:35:10,168 --> 01:35:11,278
<i>With only minutes</i>

1726
01:35:11,302 --> 01:35:12,570
<i>of racing left here
at Daytona,</i>

1727
01:35:12,670 --> 01:35:14,605
<i>a pitched battle for the lead
is being waged</i>

1728
01:35:14,705 --> 01:35:17,810
<i>as the number 98 Ford makes
an incredible late surge.</i>

1729
01:35:17,910 --> 01:35:19,778
- What's happening?
- He's moving up.

1730
01:35:19,878 --> 01:35:22,089
<i>...entering the front
tri-oval, Ken Miles' desperate bid</i>

1731
01:35:22,113 --> 01:35:23,714
<i>for the win
may prove to be...</i>

1732
01:35:32,190 --> 01:35:33,190
Come on now!

1733
01:35:33,224 --> 01:35:35,193
White flag! Last lap!

1734
01:35:40,698 --> 01:35:43,000
Miles is pushing him. Hard.

1735
01:35:53,511 --> 01:35:55,179
That's it, girl.

1736
01:36:05,656 --> 01:36:07,391
<i>Ken Miles drafts Walt Hansgen</i>

1737
01:36:07,492 --> 01:36:09,293
<i>coming into the final turn.</i>

1738
01:36:35,720 --> 01:36:36,788
Come on. Come on.

1739
01:36:40,024 --> 01:36:42,426
What the hell?

1740
01:36:50,002 --> 01:36:51,369
Come on.

1741
01:36:51,702 --> 01:36:53,037
All right.

1742
01:36:57,241 --> 01:36:58,576
Look at this now.

1743
01:37:03,414 --> 01:37:04,414
Damn it!

1744
01:37:12,323 --> 01:37:13,792
Yeah!

1745
01:37:13,892 --> 01:37:16,227
<i>Ken Miles
takes the checkered flag,</i>

1746
01:37:16,327 --> 01:37:18,362
<i>bringing glory
to Shelby American.</i>

1747
01:37:21,499 --> 01:37:22,500
How about that?

1748
01:37:32,710 --> 01:37:34,813
Reliability, strength...

1749
01:37:34,913 --> 01:37:35,913
Yes, Leo.

1750
01:37:35,914 --> 01:37:37,783
<i>Mr. Ford, sir, we won.</i>

1751
01:37:38,951 --> 01:37:39,951
Uh-huh.

1752
01:37:40,018 --> 01:37:42,153
We won! Ford won Daytona.

1753
01:37:42,253 --> 01:37:44,022
Hot damn.

1754
01:37:44,121 --> 01:37:45,791
And which team was it, Leo?

1755
01:37:47,191 --> 01:37:49,761
Shelby American.
Miles driving.

1756
01:37:51,529 --> 01:37:52,831
Son of a bitch.

1757
01:37:53,598 --> 01:37:55,242
All right.

1758
01:37:55,266 --> 01:37:56,701
Where the hell is he?

1759
01:37:56,802 --> 01:37:58,569
Hang on, I see him. Hey, wait.

1760
01:37:58,669 --> 01:38:00,973
Someone lost a bulldog
on the beach.

1761
01:38:02,741 --> 01:38:04,575
No, no. Come on. Come on.

1762
01:38:05,409 --> 01:38:08,512
Come on.
Let's go. Let's go.

1763
01:38:08,613 --> 01:38:11,482
Someone get this man a drink.
Someone get him a drink.

1764
01:38:27,164 --> 01:38:28,366
Oi.

1765
01:38:29,266 --> 01:38:31,535
In bed, you.
What are you doing?

1766
01:38:32,104 --> 01:38:33,604
Dirty stop out.

1767
01:38:34,006 --> 01:38:35,040
I was...

1768
01:38:35,841 --> 01:38:38,744
drawing a map, so I could
follow you on Le Mans.

1769
01:38:39,210 --> 01:38:40,478
Mmm.

1770
01:38:42,513 --> 01:38:44,482
Look at that.

1771
01:38:45,851 --> 01:38:47,385
That is spot on.

1772
01:38:47,485 --> 01:38:49,720
You are a dab hand,
very accurate.

1773
01:38:51,722 --> 01:38:53,091
Tell me about the track.

1774
01:38:53,190 --> 01:38:54,893
No, I can't, Petey.

1775
01:38:54,993 --> 01:38:56,227
Please.

1776
01:39:04,702 --> 01:39:06,872
Well, you start
at the start line.

